# Frontend theming (light / dark)

The UI is **Bootstrap 5 + react-bootstrap**, not MUI or Tailwind. Theme switching is **not** `theme.palette` / `sx`.

## How theme works

1. **Source of truth:** [`src/frontend/src/index.css`](../../src/frontend/src/index.css) — `:root` (light) and `[data-theme="dark"]` redefine `--bs-*`, `--rh-*`, and Recon aliases.
2. **React hook:** [`ThemeContext.js`](../../src/frontend/src/contexts/ThemeContext.js) sets `document.body.setAttribute('data-theme', 'light' | 'dark')` and `localStorage['recon-theme']`.
3. **Selector rule:** Any CSS that targets dark mode must use **`[data-theme="dark"]`** (variables are on `body`, inherited by the tree). Do **not** use `:root[data-theme=…]` unless you also set `data-theme` on `<html>` (this app does not).

## Decision tree: “How do I color this?”

1. **Default:** Use **semantic Bootstrap** (`Card`, `Button`, `text-muted`, `border`, `bg-*` overrides already wired in `index.css`).
2. **Surfaces / borders / text in inline styles:** Use **`var(--bs-body-color)`**, **`var(--bs-border-color)`**, **`var(--bs-card-bg)`**, **`var(--bs-text-muted)`**, etc. — never raw `#…` for neutrals.
3. **Plain CSS / `.css` files next to components:** Use **`var(--bs-*)`** / **`var(--rh-*)`** only. Do not duplicate parallel light/dark hex palettes; rely on the global variable flip.
4. **Binary UI that CSS cannot express:** `useTheme()` → `isLight` / `isDark` (navbar `variant`, hero image swap). Keep this **narrow**.
5. **SVG / canvas / chart strokes** where you need a JS object: import **[`chartTheme.js`](../../src/frontend/src/utils/chartTheme.js)** or follow the same `var(--bs-*)` strings as inline SVG attributes (supported in modern browsers).
6. **Workflow canvas nodes (React Flow):** Use **`workflowNodeTheme.js`** shared tokens and **`var(--bs-*)`** in inline `style` gradients — avoid `isDark ? '#…' : '#…'` for layout chrome.

## Token reference (most-used)

| Token | Use |
|-------|-----|
| `--bs-body-bg`, `--bs-body-color` | Page background, primary text |
| `--bs-card-bg`, `--bs-card-border-color` | Cards, panels |
| `--bs-border-color` | Dividers, 1px borders |
| `--bs-text-muted` | Secondary / helper text |
| `--bs-link-color`, `--bs-link-hover-color` | Links, link-like hover |
| `--bs-primary`, `--bs-primary-rgb` | Brand accent (with `rgba(var(--bs-primary-rgb), α)`) |
| `--bs-success`, `--bs-danger`, `--bs-warning` (+ `-rgb`) | Semantic states, charts |
| `--bs-table-hover-bg`, `--bs-subtle-hover-bg` | Row / list hover |
| `--bs-pre-bg`, `--bs-pre-color` | Code / pre blocks |
| `--bs-input-bg`, `--bs-input-border-color` | Form fields |
| `--bs-secondary-bg`, `--bs-tertiary-bg` | Subtle strips, table headers |
| `--rh-cyan`, `--rh-cyan-rgb`, `--rh-on-cyan` | Logo / neon accents |
| `--rh-highlight-bg` | Soft “info” chip / highlight background |
| `--rh-mark-bg`, `--rh-mark-color` | Search / text mark highlights |
| `--rh-overlay-scrim`, `--rh-shadow-color` | Sidebars, overlays, soft elevation |
| `--rh-dashboard-panel-shadow` | Dashboard cards (`.dashboard-panel`) and workflow builder section panels — borderless, same layered shadow in light/dark |
| `--rh-code-bg`, `--rh-code-color` | Inline code where pre tokens differ |
| `--rh-table-border-color` | Table **row** lines (and list-group); stronger in light — no inset “frame” around tables |
| `--rh-table-header-bg` | `thead` band — set **explicit hex per theme** in `:root` / `[data-theme="dark"]`; do **not** define on `:root` as only `var(--bs-secondary-bg)` (it resolves with light `--bs-secondary-bg` and that **computed** value inherits into dark, gray-washing headers) |

## Palette summary (index.css)

Light (`:root`): body `#edf1f7`; card `#f7f9fc`; thead `#dce3ef` (`--rh-table-header-bg`); borders `rgba(0, 151, 167, 0.22–0.28)`; primary `#0097a7` / `rgb(0, 151, 167)`; shared brand `--rh-cyan` / `--rh-purple` unchanged.

Dark (`[data-theme="dark"]`): body `#121d32`; card `#1c2d4a`; table surface `#18243d`; thead band `#223651` (`--rh-table-header-bg`); elevated `#233451`; `--rh-table-border-color` for row lines; card rim cyan ~`0.4` alpha; muted text `#9abdd0`; neon `--bs-primary` / `--bs-info` for fills and dark-nav chrome.

Semantic **outlined cards** (`.card.border-*`): **light + dark** use one rim — `var(--bs-card-border-color)` (markup keeps `border-primary` / `border-danger` / … without rainbow rims). **Dashboard** uses `.dashboard-panel` instead of `border-*`: **borderless** with a soft **shadow** (light: `var(--rh-shadow-color)` stack; dark: deeper neutral shadow so panels lift off `#121d32`). Headers keep a thin `border-bottom` for separation.

**Dark-mode links:** do not style every `a` with `!important` — that overrides `Button as={Link}` (`a.btn`); scope prose links with `:not(.btn)` (and other Bootstrap chrome) or set `a.btn` back to `var(--bs-btn-color)` / `var(--bs-btn-hover-color)`.

**Tables:** prefer horizontal row lines only; do not add inset `box-shadow` “frames” around `.table` / `.table-responsive`.

Add new **named** tokens in `index.css` (`:root` + `[data-theme="dark"]`) if a pattern repeats; do not scatter one-off hex.

## Banned patterns

- **Hex / rgb literals** in `style={{}}` for neutrals (`#f8f9fa`, `#dee2e6`, `#6c757d`, …).
- **Copy-paste Bootstrap default blues** (`#0d6efd`, `#1976d2`) — the app brand is **cyan / purple** via `--bs-primary` and overrides.
- **Parallel “light palette” + “dark palette”** blocks in component CSS with hardcoded grays — use variables only.
- **Assuming `data-theme` on `:root`** for app theme (use `body` / descendants).

## Correct examples

**Inline surface + border**

```jsx
<div style={{ backgroundColor: 'var(--bs-card-bg)', border: '1px solid var(--bs-border-color)' }}>
```

**Hover via DOM (reset to inherit default)**

```js
el.style.color = 'var(--bs-link-color)';
el.style.color = '';
```

**Component CSS**

```css
.panel-header {
  background-color: var(--bs-secondary-bg);
  color: var(--bs-body-color);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--bs-border-color);
}
```

**Bootstrap utilities:** `bg-light` / `bg-white` are overridden for dark mode in `index.css` — acceptable for markup; still avoid **inline** light-only hex.

## Testing checklist (before merging UI)

1. Toggle **light → dark → light** in the navbar; no white “holes,” invisible text, or wrong borders.
2. Hit **workflow builder**, **screenshots** viewers, **admin** tables, and any page you touched.
3. If you added **SVG**: confirm strokes/fills in both themes (try `var(--bs-*)` first).

